  "title": "HR COORDINATOR",
  "description": "<p><strong>Roles & Responsibilities</strong></p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Serve  as the primary contact for deployed IT resources</li><li>Handle employee queries related to a<strong>ttendance, leave, access, onboarding, and\noffboardin</strong>g</li><li>Maintain accurate records of resource deployment and allocation</li><li>Receive and resolve day-to-day staff concerns</li><li>Escalate issues to the Senior Manager when required</li><li>Ensure timely follow-up and closure of issues</li><li>Coordinate with <strong>client stakeholders, internal HR/Admin teams, and vendors</strong></li><li>Ensure compliance with client processes and operational requirements</li><li>Follow <strong>SOPs,workflows, and escalation</strong> procedures</li><li>Track timesheets, approvals, access, and compliance items</li><li>Prepare regular operational and staffing reports</li><li>Obtain resource requirements from hiring/project managers</li><li>Coordinate with outsourcing vendors for staffing needs</li><li>Support process standardization and documentation</li><li>Assist in internal and external audits</li></ul><p><u><strong>Requirements</strong></u></p><ul><li>Experience in administrative operations, resource coordination, or HR support</li><li>Good organizational and documentation abilities</li><li>Ability to handle multiple stakeholders and priorities</li><li>Attention to detail and problem-solving skills</li></ul>",
